sample.csv
{noformat}
Assignee, Issue Key, Issue Type, Summary, Description, Attachment, Attachment, Attachment, Comment
Commander, CIAS-26, Task, "Tanks", "Tanks!!!", "http://www.example.com/Tank.png", "http://www.example2.com/Tank.png", "http://www.example3.com/Tank.png",
{noformat}
Now, trick is that all these three attachments have the same "name": {{Tank.png}}. Now, if you import such issue for the first time everything is OK - you have an issue with three tanks attached. However, if you delete one or two attachments from that issue and try to re-import, you won't re-attach the deleted Tank.png's - reason is:
{noformat}
2014-01-23 15:30:20,474 INFO - Importing issue: ExternalIssue{externalId=autoid-6026073560725519512, summary=Czolgi, issueType=3}
2014-01-23 15:30:26,052 INFO - Attachment 'Tank.png' of issue 'CIAS-26' already exists. Skipping
2014-01-23 15:30:26,052 INFO - Attachment 'Tank.png' of issue 'CIAS-26' already exists. Skipping
2014-01-23 15:30:26,052 INFO - Attachment 'Tank.png' of issue 'CIAS-26' already exists. Skipping
{noformat}
Ah, the importer decided that all these Tank.png are the same, whether they not - each one represent different image.

We could fix this by downloading all of the attachments during issue-update and e.g. check their HASH.

